    b.
        Magnesium loses two electrons to become an ion [2,8]^{2+}; oxygen gains two electrons to become the ion with configuration [2,8]^{2-}
    c.
        i.
            Because magnesium is more reactive than carbon
        ii.
            Magnesium conducts electricity because it is bonded metallically, there is a sea of delocalized electrons which are free to move to carry charge and hence conduct electricity.

            Magnesium Chloride conducts electricity when molten because, when molten, the magnesium chloride ions are no-longer held in place by the forces of the giant ionic lattice and so the ions are free to move to carry charge and hence conduct electricity (in contrast, were it to be solid, the ions would be held in place in a giant ionic lattice and magnesium chloride would not conduct electricity as there would be neither electrons nor ions that are free to move to carry charge)
    d.
        i.
            Because magnesium ions gain electrons to become magnesium, and reduction is gain of electrons
